Package: GLMAEDr
Title: Run the General Lake Model (GLM-AED) Executable
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("R. Quinn Thomas", email = "r.quinn.thomas@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Provides an R interface to the General Lake Model (GLM) coupled
    with the Aquatic EcoDynamics (AED) library. GLM is compiled from source
    on first use via glm_install(), producing a native binary that runs
    without code-signing restrictions. Supports macOS, Ubuntu Linux, and
    Windows (via RTools).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://flare-forecast.github.io/GLMAEDr,
    https://github.com/FLARE-forecast/GLMAEDr
BugReports: https://github.com/FLARE-forecast/GLMAEDr/issues
Imports:
    cli,
    processx,
    tools
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
